cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SD

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and tracking, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of reinforcement learning algorithms to learn an optimal decision-making policy also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning algorithms suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The focus on decision-making and optimization suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. Finally, the use of streaming videos as a data source suggests that it could belong to the cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) category.
